dt: {bc}any of a family (Sturnidae, especially genus {it}Sturnus{/it}) of usually dark gregarious oscine birds
{bc}a dark brown or in summer glossy greenish-black European bird ({it}S. vulgaris{/it}) naturalized nearly worldwide and often considered a pest

et: Middle English, from Old English {it}stærlinc{/it}, from {it}stær{/it} starling + {it}-ling, -linc{/it} -ling; akin to Old High German {it}stara{/it} starling, Latin {it}sturnus{/it}
shortdef: any of a family (Sturnidae, especially genus Sturnus) of usually dark gregarious oscine birds; especially : a dark brown or in summer glossy greenish-black European bird (S. vulgaris) naturalized nearly worldwide and often considered a pest
